pddl.prompt:
You are orchestrator. Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Agents' private information summaries:
{agents->agent_1->private_information}
{agents->agent_2->private_information}
{agents->agent_3->private_information}
Global goal:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Received inputs from agents:
{plan_agent_1}
{plan_agent_2}
{plan_agent_3}
Task: Integrate these agent-specific primitive moves, resolve any conflicts or deferred moves, and produce:
1) A PDDL domain and problem pair (enclosed in <domain></domain> and <problem></problem>) suitable for FastDownward that models three agents with distinct action names and the Tower of Hanoi rules for 20 labeled disks and 3 pegs.
2) An explicit, ordered list of primitive moves (one per line) in the format 'agent_i: move disk X from peg1 to peg2' that, when executed in order, achieves the stated goal configuration.
If you must reorder or assign particular moves to agents to respect their permitted disk sets, do so and document the assignment decisions briefly before the PDDL output.
